GateDocument.TextWithNodes: Call For Papers MIS'99 Fifth International Workshop on MULTIMEDIA INFORMATION SYSTEMS October 21 - 23 , 1999 Miramonte Resort Indian Wells , Palm Springs Desert , California Workshop Home Page : http : / / www . cs . ucr . edu / ~ mis 99 MIS'99 is the fifth of a series of workshops which started in 1995 with the aim of fostering interdisciplinary discussions and research in all aspects of multimedia information systems . MIS'99 will be held between October 21 - 23 , 1999 , at the Miramonte Resort , a mediterranean style resort hotel located at Indian Wells , in the Palm Springs Desert area ( about 130 miles east of Los Angeles ) . MIS'99 follows upon the success of the four workshops in this series that were held in Arlington ( VA ) , West Point ( NY ) , Como ( Italy ) and Istanbul ( Turkey ) . As in the past , this is a focused workshop , consisting of participants drawn from a wide variety of disciplines such as : - databases , - networks , - operating systems , - graphics and visualization , - artificial intelligence , - real-time systems , - theory , - algorithms , etc . all of whom are engaged in research on one or more aspects of multimedia systems . INSTRUCTIONS FOR AUTHORS : Authors are invited to submit extended abstracts ( maximum 6 pages ) or one-page descriptions of panel proposals by May 10 , 1999 . Selection will be based on originality and contribution to the field . Manuscripts must be in English , typed in double spaced format in 12 point font . Each extended abstract should have an extra cover page with name , title , and address ( including e-mail address ) of the contact author and an abstract of no more than 200 words . Each panel proposal should include a list of proposed panelists . Electronic submissions are STRONGLY encouraged ! Please send the postscript file of your short paper or panel proposal by May 10 , 1999 , to : mis 99 @ csmmc . dy . csdo . ^ ^ ^ ^ ^ ^ ^ ^ ^ ^ ^ ^ ^ If electronic submission is not possible , please send six copies of the short paper or panel proposal to the following postal address : Prof .
